    <section>
        <h2>About Him</h2>
        <p>
            Sardar Vallabai Patel is remembered as a very strong and dynamic freedom fighter of India and had actively contributed to the
            Indian Freedom Movement. Sardar Patel was one of the most eminent 
            and prominent leaders of the Indian Freedom struggle.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Why He Inspires Me</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>He played a critical role in India's independence movement and brought together the country's princely states into a single nation.</li> 
            <li> His firm leadership and vision shaped modern India. The Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel statue in Gujarat honors his legacy.</li>
            <li>He is remembered for his honesty, unity, and service to the nation.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Key Achievements</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>India's first Deputy Prime Minister and Home Minister in integrating.</li>
            <li>Preventing fragmentation; leading successful peasant movements like the Bardoli Satyagraha.</li>
            <li>Organizing refugee relief and restoring peace post-partition.</li>
            <li>Earning him the title 'Sardar".</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>His Inspirational Quote</h2>
        <p class="quote">
            “ Unity, Strength, Duty, and Self-reliance.”
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Legacy</h2>
        <p>
            Sardar Patel held that Fundamental Rights and Liberty are essential pre-
requisites for the development of the individual and a nation. His devotion to
work for the farmers’ rights gave Patel the title “Sardar”.
        </p>
    </section>

